
feature:
user survay -> add skill
skill new -> add to sanitize queue
existing skill -> add to user skills
skill from sanitize queue -> llm checks if it can be added to synonyms of existing skills or is a new valid skill
if can be added to existing -> add to aka and add the og skill to user
if new skill entirly -> create a new skill


techinical details:
add a method in CanonicalSkill to search skill by name ie in the name field also in synonyms field
llm prompt to take a skill input and o/p valid CanonicalSkill data
llm tool that pulls skills from table along with description -- param has limit that the llm will use to get data in chunks so to save token spend
llm call (worker class) that has i/p skill entered by user and  o/p should be the canonical skill obj (existing/new) updated synonyms only if the input is very different from existing synonyms
instead of static skills pass Jobs.skills to developer during survay (grouped by credit title)
if user selects the skill from the given list add id to the obj -- in update_from_input of developerintentsurvay if we get id in skill add skill to dev else call searchskill of CanonicalSkill to get the skill obj; if still no skill then pass the data to llm call (using worker task and the WorkerTaskTarget set to the developer who created the skill)
) to get a sanatize and get a new skill
create a collect task to collect and create the sanatized skill and attach it to developer






